  "reasoning": "The article provides kinetic parameters (Km and Vmax) for the peroxidase‑like (POD) and catalase‑like (CAT) activities of four vanadium oxide nanozymes (Vnps‑I, II, III, IV).  \nFor POD the substrate is H₂O₂ (varied) and TMB is used as a constant co‑substrate (5 mM). Therefore the reaction type is **H2O2+TMB**. The kinetic assays were performed with a catalyst concentration of 100 µg mL⁻¹ (0.1 mg mL⁻¹) at two pH values (7.4 and 6.0). The tables give Km (mM) and Vmax (M·s⁻¹) for each nanozyme/pH condition, together with the range of H₂O₂ concentrations used (C_min–C_max).  \n\nFor CAT the substrate is H₂O₂ only (no co‑substrate), so the reaction type is left null. The same catalyst concentration (0.1 mg mL⁻¹) was used, and H₂O₂ concentrations from 50 mM to 600 mM were employed (C_min = 50 mM, C_max = 600 mM). Km is reported in mM and Vmax in mg L⁻¹ min⁻¹. Kinetic data are available for each nanozyme at pH 7.4; for Vnps‑I, II also at pH 6.0, while Vnps‑III and IV were only measured at pH 7.4.  \n\nParticle size information from TEM/SEM is included (≈10 nm for Vnps‑I, II, III; ≈55 nm for Vnps‑IV). The chemical formula of the material is taken as **V2O5** (the vanadium oxide precursor). Other fields (syngony, surface, etc.) are not reported and are left null.\n\nEach experiment is represented as a separate object following the NanozymeExperiment schema."
